---
import PageLayout from "../layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import Subheading from "../components/Subheading.astro";
---

<PageLayout title="Privacy Policy">
  <div class="article-wrapper">
    <article id="privacy-policy" class="classic-bg">
      <Subheading title="Privacy Policy" />
      <foreground>
        <text-container>

          <p> Technolgap is committed to protecting the privacy and security of personal information held
            about its patrons. Our purpose is to assure anyone who does business and volunteers with us
            that Technolgap complies with Canadaâ€™s Personal Information Protection and Electronic
            Documents Act (PIPEDA) and provincial guidelines. This policy explains how we collect, use,
            disclose and safeguard personal information. </p>
          
          <h3> Definition Of Personal Information </h3>
          <p> Personal information is any information that is identifiable to you as an individual. This may
            include, but is not limited to, your name, gender, age, date of birth, language of correspondence,
            mailing address, telephone number, fax number, email address, and membership in an
            organization. </p>

          <h3> Collection Of Information: </h3>
          <p> We may collect personal information that you voluntarily provide to us when you express an
            interest in volunteering with us or contacting us.
            The personal information that we collect depends on the context of your interactions with us and
            the Site, but may include: </p>
          <bullet> Name </bullet>
          <bullet> Email address </bullet>
          <bullet> Phone number </bullet>
          <bullet> Post secondary institution</bullet>

          <h3> Use Of Information </h3>
          <p> We use the information we collect in the following ways: </p>
          <bullet> To communicate with you, including providing you with updates and information </bullet>
          <bullet> To improve our website and present its contents to you </bullet>
          <bullet> To comply with legal obligations </bullet>

          <h3> Disclosure Of Information </h3>
          <p> We may share your personal information with third parties who perform services for us or on our
            behalf, such as payment processing, data analysis, email delivery, hosting services, customer
            service, and marketing assistance. </p>

          <h3> Your Rights </h3>
          <p> You have the right to: </p>
          <bullet> Access your personal information </bullet>
          <bullet> Correct any personal information we hold about you </bullet>
          <bullet> Request that we delete your personal information </bullet>
          <bullet> Object to the processing of your personal information </bullet>

          <h3> Reporting Violations </h3>
          <p> If you encounter or witness any violations of this code of conduct, please report them
            immediately to info@technolgap.org. All reports will be handled with confidentiality and
            sensitivity. We reserve the right and responsibility to remove comments or other contributions
            that are not aligned with this code of conduct, or to ban temporarily or permanently any
            members for other behaviors that are deemed inappropriate, threatening, offensive, or harmful. </p>

          <h3> Changes To Privacy Policy </h3>
          <p> We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time in order to reflect, for example, changes to
            our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. </p>

          <h3> Contact Us </h3>
          <p> If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at: <b>info@technolgap.org</b> </p>

        </text-container>
      </foreground>
  </div>
</PageLayout>

<style>
  article {
    padding-bottom: 5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 0;
    text-align: center;

    min-height: 100vh;
    background-size: cover;
    background-color: white;
    background-color: transparent;
    box-shadow: none;
    background-position: top center;
    background-repeat: no-repeat;
    background-size: 100% auto;
  }
  .article-wrapper {
    background-color: white;
  }

  #privacy-policy foreground {
    display: grid;
    background-color: #64a8a2;
    border-radius: 20px;
    row-gap: 5px;
    box-shadow: 0 7px 10px 1px #898989;
    margin: 0 50px;
    border: solid 5px #fee8f5;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  #privacy-policy h3 {
    font-size: 30px;
    text-shadow: 
    1px 1px 0px #FFBCE5,
    -1px -1px 0px #FFBCE5,
    1px -1px 0px #FFBCE5,
    -1px 1px 0px #FFBCE5;
    color: white;
  }
  #privacy-policy p {
    color: #ffffff;
    font-size: 18px;
    text-align: left;
    margin-left: 12rem;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    margin-right: 12rem;
  }
  #privacy-policy p-bullet {
    color: #ffffff;
    font-size: 18px;
    text-align: left;
    margin-left: 12rem;
    /* margin-top: 2rem; */
    /* margin-bottom: 2rem; */
    margin-right: 12rem;
  }
  #privacy-policy bullet {
    display: list-item;
    list-style-type: disc;
    margin-left: 13rem;
    margin-top: 0.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: #ffffff;
    font-size: 18px;
    text-align: left;
    margin-right: 12rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 800px) {
    #privacy-policy h3 {
      font-size: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
    #privacy-policy p,
    #privacy-policy bullet {
      font-size: 14px;
      margin: 1rem;
      margin-left: 5rem;
      margin-right: 5rem;
    }
  }
  @media (max-width: 450px) {
    #privacy-policy p,
    #privacy-policy bullet {
      margin: 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>